org.jboss.windup.graph

Class GraphTypeManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jboss.windup.graph.GraphTypeManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.tinkerpop.frames.FrameInitializer, com.tinkerpop.frames.modules.TypeResolver

    public class GraphTypeManager
extends Object
implements com.tinkerpop.frames.modules.TypeResolver, com.tinkerpop.frames.FrameInitializer
    Windup's implementation of extended type handling for TinkerPop Frames. This allows storing multiple types based on the @TypeValue.value(), also in the type property (see WindupFrame.TYPE_PROP.

      • addTypeToElement

        public void addTypeToElement(String typeString,
                             com.tinkerpop.blueprints.Element element)
        Adds the type value to the field denoting which type the element represents. This is similar to addTypeToElement(Class, Element), however it uses a String type instead. The String type will be looked up from the type registry to determine the class type to use.
